title: Grateful Dead Live at Aladdin Theater on 1981-08-31
lineage: CD -> Adobe Audition v3.0 -> Samplitude Professional v11.1 -> FLAC
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, Jack A Roe-> El Paso, Candyman-> Little Red Rooster, Loser, Cassidy, Althea, Let It Grow-> Deal

Set 2

Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Good Time Blues-> Morning Dew-> Playin' In The Band-> Around & Around-> Johnny B. Goode, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
nice upgrade! Great show from a great year. Unusual set list, GREAT first set! 

Once again, Charlie Miller has done a wonderful job transferring (can we call it mastering?) this show. The transitions between the SBD and AUD patches are well done. THe audience source for the patches sounds way better on this version -- the sound quality is definitely better here than the other versions for this date.
great fun Dead at the Aladdin,M Dew ,Scar Fire what else you need to know ,too much fun , needless to say security was not really ready for us!

RL and Mary's wedding we were all in one of those caesar palace suites with a few bathtubs filled with ice and beer, Big George from virginia handing out the barley pops with one of his shit eating grins, atom ant, BT, Felix, Tommy Greenleaf and the crew from the YACK VAN all play'n they love each other as the bride and groom made their entrance. wonder if they stayed together?
i was 16 and had to hitch back to nyc for 11th grade. cant imagine a 16year old these days pulling that off. they can barley wipe their butt if they don't have a phone to tell them how to do it now.
